summary: you know what I really detest about the finale?? it's the fact that there are so many loose ends. I mean even if you just look...
body: you know what I really detest about the finale?? it’s the fact that there are so many loose ends. I mean even if you just look at the surface level, there are so many unanswered questions about drogon, dorne, iron islands, bran’s military power, north’s sudden independence, rebuilding of the seven kingdoms, the dothraki/unsullied, meereen and so many more issues that I can’t remember off the top of my head. these questions aren’t the type of things that can just be left up to the viewer’s interpretation and that just makes everything feel so superficial and unsatisfying.

summary: The Relationships of Blackwater: Jon/Ygritte Dislike at first sight. Ygritte is loud and stubborn... Jon is quiet and stubborn....
caption:
The Relationships of Blackwater: Jon/Ygritte

Dislike at first sight. Ygritte is loud and stubborn… Jon is quiet and stubborn. When the band falls apart, they cling to each other. As the others slowly grow back together, they fall in love - and are secretly together for months before Jon accidentally spills during a reunion interview.

“You’re going to kill me, Jon Snow. But what a way to go.”
